WEBVTT

00:06.484 --> 00:06.702
.

00:06.745 --> 00:09.661
- This contortionist clown,
I made him up

00:09.705 --> 00:13.013
when I was a kid, and then,
this figure appeared.

00:13.056 --> 00:14.579
- You have a condition.
- What?

00:14.623 --> 00:17.234
- I know,
because I have it, too.

00:17.278 --> 00:20.281
[wood creaking]

00:20.324 --> 00:22.239
- You're the woman
my husband has a kid with.

00:22.283 --> 00:25.677
- No, it's not Tom's.
He just wanted it to be.

00:25.721 --> 00:29.377
Trust gets broken,
but you can rebuild it.

00:29.420 --> 00:32.249
- What if you can't?
[grunting]

00:32.293 --> 00:33.729
- You and I can do it,

00:33.772 --> 00:35.296
but you got to do everything
I tell you to.

00:35.339 --> 00:38.299
[dramatic music]

00:38.342 --> 00:40.257
Picture it in your mind.

00:40.301 --> 00:43.217
- [heavy breathing]

00:43.260 --> 00:44.566
- You helped again.

00:44.609 --> 00:46.176
- My first creation, Tall Boy,

00:46.220 --> 00:48.178
he did some
not-so-great things.

00:48.222 --> 00:50.093
- [grunting]

00:50.137 --> 00:52.835
- I know who you are.
He's my brother.

00:52.878 --> 00:54.271
- Half-brother.

00:54.315 --> 00:56.447
I can literally
make doors with my mind

00:56.491 --> 00:58.232
that monsters come out of.

00:58.275 --> 01:00.103
- Oh, God!
- You really think they can

01:00.147 --> 01:02.410
just haul me away
in the back of a cop car?

01:02.453 --> 01:06.109
- Stay back, stay back, no!
[screaming]

01:08.285 --> 01:11.245
[soft music]

01:11.288 --> 01:18.556
♪

02:09.216 --> 02:11.174
- [grunts]

02:17.049 --> 02:21.315
What the fuck?
- All's fair in love and war.

02:21.358 --> 02:22.838
Right, Tom?

02:22.881 --> 02:24.056
[drink slurps]

02:24.100 --> 02:26.450
- Did you just go
to Stuckyburger?

02:26.494 --> 02:28.583
After you killed those cops?

02:30.454 --> 02:33.196
- I need my strength.

02:33.240 --> 02:34.850
I guess I could've sent
Tall Boy,

02:34.893 --> 02:37.157
but he has a hard time
keeping a low profile.

02:37.200 --> 02:39.550
♪

02:39.594 --> 02:41.204
[laughs]

02:41.248 --> 02:43.380
I didn't get you anything.

02:45.382 --> 02:47.602
- Where are we?

02:47.645 --> 02:49.517
- Your wife's house,
believe it or not.

02:49.560 --> 02:54.217
My dad--our dad
left everything to her.

02:54.261 --> 02:55.697
Yeah, along with
a lot of other stuff.

02:55.740 --> 02:59.440
This whole development
belongs to her now.

02:59.483 --> 03:01.529
I'd congratulate you on
probably getting half of it

03:01.572 --> 03:05.054
in the divorce, but, uh,
something tells me

03:05.097 --> 03:09.798
you're probably not
going to live long enough--

03:09.841 --> 03:11.887
[exhales]

03:11.930 --> 03:14.759
- Everything okay?

03:14.803 --> 03:19.590
- I'm fine.
- Pull a muscle or something?

03:21.940 --> 03:24.378
- Thanks for asking.

03:24.421 --> 03:26.075
[sighs]

03:26.118 --> 03:27.772
Look.

03:27.816 --> 03:30.558
[tense music]

03:30.601 --> 03:35.215
I know that this might
be hard for you

03:35.258 --> 03:38.957
to wrap your head around.

03:39.001 --> 03:42.787
But I love her.

03:44.398 --> 03:46.574
- You love Jillian?

03:46.617 --> 03:49.490
- I do.
I really do.

03:49.533 --> 03:54.669
I love her in a pure,
uncomplicated way.

03:54.712 --> 03:56.279
- You don't even know her, man.

03:56.323 --> 04:00.152
- Nevertheless, we have
a fundamental connection.

04:00.196 --> 04:02.677
- Yeah, she doesn't
feel that way.

04:02.720 --> 04:04.940
- You know, the whole thing
really fucking baffles me,

04:04.983 --> 04:07.334
if I'm being honest with you.
- Yeah, you and me both, man.

04:07.377 --> 04:09.727
- No, I--

04:09.771 --> 04:12.164
I mean I get that she didn't
know she was special, right?

04:12.208 --> 04:14.297
I mean, sure.

04:14.341 --> 04:19.041
But deep down,
she must have known.

04:19.084 --> 04:23.611
And yet, she ends up with you.

04:23.654 --> 04:26.614
But the more I think about it,
the more sense it makes.

04:26.657 --> 04:28.659
You and her, you were friends
when you were kids, right?

04:28.703 --> 04:32.010
So there's that--that bond.

04:32.054 --> 04:34.796
Dad left when she was what?
She was eight?

04:34.839 --> 04:37.842
Any guy she meets after that,
she's going to be thinking

04:37.886 --> 04:40.236
"Is he going to
break my heart, too?"

04:40.280 --> 04:43.674
But not you.

04:43.718 --> 04:47.156
You're from before.
You're from when she felt safe.

04:47.199 --> 04:49.027
♪

04:49.071 --> 04:51.769
That's all you are, man.

04:51.813 --> 04:54.468
You just...

04:54.511 --> 04:56.121
you're the safe choice.

04:56.165 --> 04:57.558
[groans]

04:57.601 --> 05:00.561
[dramatic music]

05:00.604 --> 05:06.088
♪

05:06.131 --> 05:08.656
- Go, go!

05:08.699 --> 05:10.353
Get him!

05:10.397 --> 05:17.578
♪

06:31.303 --> 06:34.263
[tense music]

06:34.306 --> 06:41.531
♪

07:02.770 --> 07:04.902
- What are you doing here?

07:04.946 --> 07:07.949
- Did you see anybody tonight?

07:07.992 --> 07:10.299
- I see you.

07:10.342 --> 07:14.129
- Before me.

07:14.172 --> 07:17.001
Was anybody here?

07:17.045 --> 07:24.095
♪

07:26.663 --> 07:29.666
- Look, I just got here.

07:31.712 --> 07:34.976
- I'm looking for--

07:35.019 --> 07:36.978
- What the hell?

07:37.021 --> 07:39.502
Hey, last time I checked,
this ain't Halloween.

07:39.546 --> 07:40.982
Y'all got to go home.

07:41.025 --> 07:43.550
What, is this some sort
of joke or something?

07:43.593 --> 07:45.639
- No, no, no.
- Hey, hey, no, no--

07:45.682 --> 07:47.118
[groaning]

07:47.162 --> 07:49.730
[dramatic music]

07:49.773 --> 07:53.342
- Shit!
- [groans]

07:53.385 --> 07:55.692
[screams]

08:25.853 --> 08:29.030
[chainsaw revs]

08:42.652 --> 08:45.350
[owl hoots]

08:49.180 --> 08:51.226
[chainsaw revs]

09:02.629 --> 09:04.500
[chainsaw revs]

09:04.544 --> 09:05.893
[knocking]

09:05.936 --> 09:09.070
[tense music]

09:09.113 --> 09:16.164
♪

09:22.649 --> 09:26.261
- Oh, my God.
Tom...

09:26.304 --> 09:27.697
Oh, my God.

09:27.741 --> 09:29.743
[heavy breathing]

09:29.786 --> 09:31.266
What did he do to you?

09:31.309 --> 09:36.271
- I-I got away,
but they--they hurt me.

09:36.314 --> 09:39.274
[soft music]

09:39.317 --> 09:42.930
♪

09:42.973 --> 09:45.802
- Tom...

09:48.675 --> 09:51.329
We got to figure out a plan.

09:51.373 --> 09:53.636
- I love you.

09:53.680 --> 10:00.904
♪

10:02.689 --> 10:04.821
- Tom...

10:08.259 --> 10:12.002
I don't think we can get out
of here on our own, okay?

10:12.046 --> 10:15.005
I need to bring back
Pretzel Jack.

10:16.833 --> 10:19.749
He's my protector, right?
- Wait, wait, wait.

10:19.793 --> 10:24.362
- What?
- Let's just be together.

10:24.406 --> 10:27.365
[soft music]

10:27.409 --> 10:31.979
♪

10:32.022 --> 10:37.027
- Tom, I need
to do this now, okay?

10:37.071 --> 10:41.162
Just--just hold on.
Hang in there, okay?

10:41.205 --> 10:45.166
Just be present for me.
Can you do that?

10:45.209 --> 10:47.516
Oh, my God.

10:47.559 --> 10:49.779
[heavy breathing]

10:57.395 --> 11:00.355
[tense music]

11:00.398 --> 11:07.405
♪

11:32.604 --> 11:34.737
[groans]

11:40.612 --> 11:43.398
- It's okay.

11:43.441 --> 11:47.358
Babe...

11:47.402 --> 11:49.447
it's okay.

11:50.535 --> 11:52.886
It's okay.

11:52.929 --> 11:56.106
[tense music]

11:56.150 --> 11:57.891
I love you.

11:57.934 --> 12:00.763
♪

12:00.807 --> 12:03.723
- No, just--Tom,
I don't know if we're--

12:03.766 --> 12:06.029
- Shh.

12:08.075 --> 12:10.904
Let's just be together.

12:10.947 --> 12:16.083
Right here, right now.

12:16.126 --> 12:20.261
Oh, I just want to feel
what it's like to be with you.

12:22.393 --> 12:23.612
- What--

12:23.655 --> 12:26.267
[grunts]

12:26.310 --> 12:28.704
What--

12:28.748 --> 12:31.272
- Let's just be together.

12:35.232 --> 12:36.973
[grunts]

12:37.017 --> 12:39.802
[dramatic music]

12:39.846 --> 12:41.673
- [gasps]

12:41.717 --> 12:43.632
Holy shit!

12:43.675 --> 12:45.242
♪

12:45.286 --> 12:49.681
- Jill--
- No, stay away from me.

12:49.725 --> 12:53.947
- Jill, no, it's--
- Me, Tom.

12:57.864 --> 12:59.648
- You're not my Tom.

12:59.691 --> 13:02.477
♪

13:02.520 --> 13:05.523
- [grunts]

13:05.567 --> 13:08.526
[dramatic music]

13:08.570 --> 13:15.620
♪

13:27.807 --> 13:30.331
- [grunts]

13:35.031 --> 13:37.207
- [heavy breathing]

13:51.395 --> 13:53.658
[grunts]

13:57.401 --> 13:59.099
[yells]

14:39.443 --> 14:41.706
- Did he make that
or did you?

14:45.058 --> 14:49.714
I'm real, okay?
It's me.

14:49.758 --> 14:52.587
For better, for worse.

14:52.630 --> 14:56.896
- Tell me something
only you know, from our past.

14:56.939 --> 14:59.899
[tense music]

14:59.942 --> 15:05.817
♪

15:05.861 --> 15:07.471
- [grunts]

15:09.473 --> 15:12.476
I think we've dwelled enough
on the past.

15:22.573 --> 15:25.533
[soft music]

15:25.576 --> 15:27.317
♪

15:27.361 --> 15:29.667
Now that you know
it's really me,

15:29.711 --> 15:32.757
does it make you
any happier to see me?

15:32.801 --> 15:35.195
♪

15:35.238 --> 15:37.545
- Oh, my God, Tom.

15:52.821 --> 15:55.780
[dramatic music]

15:55.824 --> 16:00.829
♪

16:00.872 --> 16:03.049
- Now let's go.

16:06.704 --> 16:09.794
[tense music]

16:09.838 --> 16:17.019
♪

16:25.158 --> 16:32.382
♪

16:58.060 --> 17:00.149
- [grunts]

17:01.194 --> 17:03.413
[heavy breathing]

17:10.116 --> 17:12.814
You okay?

17:16.426 --> 17:21.605
- I killed my husband.
I'm a little shaken up.

17:23.694 --> 17:26.088
- I killed him.

17:28.438 --> 17:31.224
I like to think
there's some differences

17:31.267 --> 17:34.183
between me and that thing.

17:35.706 --> 17:39.754
- I just lost control.

17:39.797 --> 17:42.452
Something took over.

17:44.846 --> 17:46.935
I was killing you, Tom.

17:46.978 --> 17:50.765
- Look, let's just--
let's table this for now.

17:52.288 --> 17:54.769
Let's figure out
how to get out of here.

17:54.812 --> 17:57.772
[soft music]

17:57.815 --> 18:00.340
♪

18:00.383 --> 18:03.952
- What if Pretzel Jack
really had killed you?

18:03.995 --> 18:05.388
Which he almost did?

18:05.432 --> 18:07.608
Then you really would be dead
because of me.

18:07.651 --> 18:13.135
The fact that he went after you
means on some level...

18:16.486 --> 18:18.662
- You want to kill me?

18:20.403 --> 18:23.232
- You lied to me.

18:23.276 --> 18:26.366
Maybe I wanted
to kill that part of you.

18:31.588 --> 18:33.242
- Look, those things
are still out there, okay?

18:33.286 --> 18:34.939
We got to--

18:34.983 --> 18:37.855
[grunts]

18:37.899 --> 18:40.336
[sniffs]

18:40.380 --> 18:43.644
[buzz saw revs]

18:43.687 --> 18:47.082
Come on, come on.
We got to hurry.

18:47.126 --> 18:50.172
- Go.
Get help.

18:50.216 --> 18:51.826
I'm the one he wants.

18:51.869 --> 18:54.263
[soft music]

18:54.307 --> 18:56.396
- Well, he can't have you.

18:56.439 --> 19:03.707
♪

19:05.231 --> 19:08.364
- Wait.
- What?

19:08.408 --> 19:10.453
- This--this is wrong.
- No, no, no, no.

19:10.497 --> 19:13.195
Look, that's the way out.
- No, something feels wrong.

19:13.239 --> 19:15.415
Just trust me.

19:18.331 --> 19:20.507
- I knew it.

19:20.550 --> 19:24.641
You knew where I was.
You can sense me.

19:24.685 --> 19:26.861
You never would have made it.

19:26.904 --> 19:30.343
I got my--my little guys
all over the place.

19:30.386 --> 19:33.346
They're very good at hiding.

19:40.918 --> 19:43.182
[slurps drink]

19:43.225 --> 19:45.923
- Just let us go, Ian.

19:48.926 --> 19:51.364
That took a lot out of you,
didn't it?

19:51.407 --> 19:54.149
Creating that other Tom.

19:54.193 --> 19:56.238
- No, no, I'll be fine.

19:56.282 --> 19:58.458
Just need to recharge a little.

19:58.501 --> 20:00.068
Like sex, you know?

20:00.111 --> 20:03.289
If you want to try something
very ambitious,

20:03.332 --> 20:06.379
you might need a sec
to recover.

20:06.422 --> 20:09.382
- Why did you do it?

20:09.425 --> 20:12.863
Why did you make Tom?

20:12.907 --> 20:15.779
- To be with you.

20:15.823 --> 20:19.392
And you know what?
It felt good.

20:19.435 --> 20:21.176
It felt really good.

20:21.220 --> 20:22.395
I--we're supposed
to be together.

20:22.438 --> 20:24.962
I know you can feel it.

20:25.006 --> 20:29.184
I mean, don't you want to learn
to use this thing we have?

20:29.228 --> 20:31.926
It's what makes us special.

20:32.970 --> 20:35.886
- I tried to bring back
Pretzel Jack.

20:35.930 --> 20:37.540
I couldn't do it.

20:37.584 --> 20:39.760
- Would you forget about
Pretzel Jack?

20:39.803 --> 20:44.025
Let's make something new.
Something that's ours.

20:44.068 --> 20:46.288
- Right now?

20:46.332 --> 20:48.943
- Well...

20:48.986 --> 20:50.292
not while he's watching.

20:50.336 --> 20:52.076
[slurps drink]

20:52.120 --> 20:53.556
That'd just be weird.

20:53.600 --> 20:56.777
[dramatic music]

20:56.820 --> 20:59.127
♪

20:59.170 --> 21:02.478
- Tom, run, run!

21:02.522 --> 21:04.567
[buzz saw revs]

21:06.656 --> 21:08.484
- Go!

21:11.182 --> 21:12.836
[bones crack]

21:14.403 --> 21:16.318
- In there, in there.

21:16.362 --> 21:18.451
- [panting]

21:32.203 --> 21:35.859
- Oh, shit.

21:35.903 --> 21:38.819
- [grunts]

21:38.862 --> 21:41.474
- [panting]

21:45.042 --> 21:46.870
Do you see anything?

21:49.351 --> 21:51.832
So what do we do?

21:51.875 --> 21:54.530
We just--we make
another run for it?

22:00.580 --> 22:05.367
- I need to do something,
and you won't like it.

22:05.411 --> 22:07.238
- I'm sorry for
letting you believe

22:07.282 --> 22:09.240
that this is all your fault.

22:09.284 --> 22:13.157
- It's not just my fault, Tom.

22:13.201 --> 22:16.117
It's part of who I am.

22:16.160 --> 22:20.948
- You have a whole bunch
of intense shit in your head.

22:20.991 --> 22:23.690
We both do.

22:23.733 --> 22:27.694
And in your case,
sometimes, it just

22:27.737 --> 22:32.089
gets out, runs around,
kills people.

22:32.133 --> 22:36.398
But I accept that.

22:36.442 --> 22:39.749
And I love you.

22:39.793 --> 22:41.403
[sighs]

22:43.536 --> 22:48.149
This is me.
Good and bad.

22:48.192 --> 22:52.371
I was ashamed of myself.

22:52.414 --> 22:54.460
And I hid that from you.

22:56.418 --> 22:59.595
And then, when you tried
to tell me your own secrets...

23:02.468 --> 23:05.253
I didn't want to hear it.

23:05.296 --> 23:07.951
And I'm sorry.

23:09.213 --> 23:11.694
So, yeah.

23:11.738 --> 23:15.959
Maybe Pretzel Jack
is part of you.

23:18.222 --> 23:21.443
But I'm the one
who brought him back out.

23:21.487 --> 23:24.098
- It comes from both of us.

23:24.141 --> 23:26.970
- [deep breath]

23:29.146 --> 23:33.455
I love you so much.
- I love you, too.

23:40.549 --> 23:43.509
[dramatic music]

23:43.552 --> 23:50.820
♪

23:52.822 --> 23:57.174
- He's coming here next.
- Come on, come on.

24:01.614 --> 24:05.444
Wait, what--
what are you doing?

24:05.487 --> 24:08.229
- I'm buying you more time.

24:10.492 --> 24:13.713
- Come back to me.
- Always.

24:21.372 --> 24:24.332
[soft music]

24:24.375 --> 24:31.600
♪

24:46.397 --> 24:48.748
- [grunts]

24:53.535 --> 24:56.495
[dramatic music]

24:56.538 --> 25:03.719
♪

25:09.246 --> 25:10.291
[door closes]

25:10.334 --> 25:13.294
[dramatic music]

25:13.337 --> 25:19.648
♪

25:19.692 --> 25:21.911
[knocking]

25:41.627 --> 25:43.367
[knocking]

25:55.379 --> 25:57.338
[knocking]

26:47.693 --> 26:50.652
[tense music]

26:50.696 --> 26:57.920
♪

27:28.777 --> 27:31.780
[tense techno music]

27:31.824 --> 27:39.048
♪

27:55.499 --> 27:57.850
- [grunts]

28:08.643 --> 28:11.733
[grunting]

28:19.959 --> 28:22.701
- [heavy breathing]

28:22.744 --> 28:28.097
♪

28:40.588 --> 28:43.025
- Wait, look.

28:43.069 --> 28:45.245
We can't kill
all of his creatures.

28:45.288 --> 28:48.988
And even if we could,
he could just keep making more.

28:55.646 --> 28:58.606
[tense music]

28:58.649 --> 29:01.827
♪

29:01.870 --> 29:04.307
- What we need to do
is kill him.

29:10.531 --> 29:14.013
- Hey, remember, we're on
the same team this time, okay?

29:15.841 --> 29:18.626
Does that mean yes?
- Yes.

29:18.669 --> 29:25.851
♪

30:30.393 --> 30:33.962
[heavy breathing]

30:38.924 --> 30:40.751
[grunting]

30:40.795 --> 30:43.754
[dramatic music]

30:43.798 --> 30:51.023
♪

31:00.249 --> 31:03.383
[tense music]

31:03.426 --> 31:10.477
♪

31:58.133 --> 32:00.744
- Jill, what?

32:00.788 --> 32:03.747
What is it?

32:03.791 --> 32:06.750
[tense music]

32:06.794 --> 32:13.975
♪

33:48.113 --> 33:55.381
♪

34:24.279 --> 34:27.239
- This one.

34:27.282 --> 34:30.242
I like it.

34:30.285 --> 34:33.114
It's clean, simple.

34:35.943 --> 34:39.164
That's why I gave it to you.

34:39.207 --> 34:43.255
- My door.
- Right?

34:43.298 --> 34:47.607
- That was you.
- No, it was you.

34:47.650 --> 34:49.739
I just--

34:49.783 --> 34:52.699
[groans]

34:52.742 --> 34:55.223
I just, uh...

34:55.267 --> 34:59.009
gave you a little push
from next door.

34:59.053 --> 35:01.142
[heavy breathing]

35:03.449 --> 35:06.626
I need you
to give me something.

35:06.669 --> 35:10.804
You got to tell me,
this--this connection.

35:10.847 --> 35:12.458
[sighs]

35:12.501 --> 35:13.894
You feel it too, right?

35:13.937 --> 35:16.636
I-I mean, I'm not--
I'm not crazy, right?

35:22.337 --> 35:24.165
- I feel it.

35:24.209 --> 35:25.471
But, Ian...

35:25.514 --> 35:27.864
You're still fucking crazy.

35:33.087 --> 35:35.263
- Okay, well...

35:35.307 --> 35:38.179
let me ask you.

35:38.223 --> 35:40.660
Where were you, Jill?

35:40.703 --> 35:44.403
Why didn't you
come looking for me?

35:50.060 --> 35:53.238
- I thought you must
be perfect.

35:53.281 --> 35:55.762
And I hated you.

35:58.591 --> 36:02.812
- Think of all the--
all the years wasted.

36:02.856 --> 36:05.989
There's so much
we could have shared.

36:06.033 --> 36:09.950
♪

36:09.993 --> 36:12.170
You could have learned to
control the shit in your head

36:12.213 --> 36:14.215
instead of
letting it control you.

36:14.259 --> 36:15.521
- I want to control
the shit in my head

36:15.564 --> 36:17.305
because I want to
protect people from it

36:17.349 --> 36:18.654
and protect myself.

36:18.698 --> 36:21.048
I don't want to
hurt people with it.

36:21.091 --> 36:24.791
And you don't
have to either, Ian.

36:24.834 --> 36:28.969
We control this.
It doesn't control us.

36:29.012 --> 36:30.710
- Would you just stop

36:30.753 --> 36:33.974
fucking pretending you're
something Tom wants you to be?

36:34.017 --> 36:36.106
[tense music]

36:36.150 --> 36:38.065
- It's just me.

36:38.108 --> 36:39.762
♪

36:39.806 --> 36:41.634
- Please.

36:41.677 --> 36:44.811
You know he just
reminds you of Dad, right?

36:44.854 --> 36:50.382
Tom reminds you of the father
who abandoned you.

36:50.425 --> 36:53.036
Who I killed for you.

36:53.080 --> 36:55.735
- You took away the only chance
I had of forgiving him.

36:55.778 --> 36:59.739
- Forgiving.
Are you fucking kidding me?

36:59.782 --> 37:03.699
♪

37:03.743 --> 37:07.616
You know,
I think I knew, deep down...

37:07.660 --> 37:11.925
when I found out
that you existed...

37:11.968 --> 37:15.581
there was only one way
this was going to end.

37:15.624 --> 37:18.236
- Ian.

37:18.279 --> 37:19.541
Stop, let go!

37:19.585 --> 37:22.762
[dramatic music]

37:22.805 --> 37:29.812
♪

37:34.164 --> 37:36.297
No, no.

37:42.999 --> 37:45.306
[grunts]

37:52.357 --> 37:55.316
[tense music]

37:55.360 --> 38:02.628
♪

38:14.509 --> 38:17.469
♪

38:17.512 --> 38:21.429
[buzz saw revs]

38:24.606 --> 38:27.957
- Stop him!
- I don't think I will.

39:07.432 --> 39:14.613
♪

39:33.588 --> 39:36.678
[screaming]

39:39.464 --> 39:42.728
No, no.

39:44.599 --> 39:46.949
[rapid breathing]

40:09.145 --> 40:13.976
♪

40:14.020 --> 40:16.979
[soft music]

40:17.023 --> 40:24.073
♪

40:27.512 --> 40:28.948
- [crying]

40:28.991 --> 40:31.429
- That's--
No, that's you.

40:31.472 --> 40:33.213
[scoffs]

40:33.256 --> 40:35.128
- Boom.

40:35.171 --> 40:37.957
Rock destroys those scissors.
- Ugh, every time.

40:38.000 --> 40:39.567
Really?
- Your turn.

40:39.611 --> 40:42.396
- Come on.
- Those are the rules.

40:42.440 --> 40:44.311
[soft music]

40:44.354 --> 40:48.184
♪

40:48.228 --> 40:50.883
- [babbles]

40:50.926 --> 40:55.670
- Hey, what's going on, bear?
Huh, what's going on, bear?

40:55.714 --> 40:58.151
Yeah, yeah.
All right.

40:58.194 --> 41:01.589
What's going on?
You want to talk to Mama?

41:01.633 --> 41:08.857
♪

41:16.865 --> 41:18.911
[exhales]

41:21.000 --> 41:23.219
- [groans]

41:23.263 --> 41:28.529
Is everything okay?
- Yeah, she's settled down.

41:28.573 --> 41:30.357
- Good job.

41:30.400 --> 41:32.359
[soft music]

41:32.402 --> 41:34.317
♪

41:34.361 --> 41:36.537
- I love you.

41:40.454 --> 41:42.978
- [snores]

41:44.893 --> 41:47.853
- [laughs]
- What's so funny?

41:47.896 --> 41:51.247
- You're just lying
here snoring.

41:51.291 --> 41:53.554
- Oh, sorry.

41:53.598 --> 41:57.558
I'm tired.
- Me, too.

41:57.602 --> 41:59.604
- Who's going to
turn out the light?

41:59.647 --> 42:01.910
- [babbles]

42:04.478 --> 42:07.742
